*QPP++ 2023 workshop at the 45th European Conference on Information 
Retrieval (ECIR)*.


*This year ECIR will be located in Dublin, Ireland,* 2-6 April 23, but 
In case you will not be able to join us in person*, ECIR 2023 is planned 
to support virtual participation in the conference and the workshops.*


The QPP++ Workshop aims at stimulating discussion on three main aspects 
concerning the future of QPP:

  * What are the*emerging QPP challenges posed by* new methods and
    technologies, including but not limited to *dense retrieval,
    contextualized embeddings*, and conversational search?
  * How might these *new techniques be used to improve the quality of QPP*?
  * Can we claim that the current techniques for *evaluating QPP* are
    effective in all arising scenarios? Can we envision new evaluation
    protocols capable of granting generalizability in new domains?

The workshop is planned to be highly interactive with half of it 
dedicated to* two focus groups* where we can discuss how to evaluate QPP 
in new domains and how to use new techniques to improve QPP.


Given your extensive work on the subject, we would like to ask you 
whether you wish to give your contribution to the success of the workshop.

We are interested in three main categories of manuscripts:

  * Full papers: up to 6 pages.
  * Short papers: up to 3 pages.
  * Discussion papers: up to 3 pages.

In particular, discussion papers require to provide your *point of view 
on the subject*, with minor experimental contributions or possibly 
*(empirically sound) failed and unsuccessful experiments *that might 
lead to a deeper understanding of the matter.

*
*

*The deadline to submit the paper is the 5th of February.*


If you wish, you can submit your contribution via Easychair at the 
following link: Submit 
<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://easychair.org/conferences/?conf=qpp2023__;!!Op6eflyXZCqGR5I!E3NDRE5487qM50Aju3AcRXdmtH3BI74SLWulXqzqsRTkScRWggpoo5yvsL8l-Stt6_RHti8y1ucoZZaOR3LAiSg$>


For more details, do not hesitate to contact me or visit our website 
https://qpp.dei.unipd.it/ 
<https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://qpp.dei.unipd.it/__;!!Op6eflyXZCqGR5I!E3NDRE5487qM50Aju3AcRXdmtH3BI74SLWulXqzqsRTkScRWggpoo5yvsL8l-Stt6_RHti8y1ucoZZaOXyWMNlI$>.


on behalf of the organizers of QPP++ Workshop@ECIR,

Guglielmo Faggioli, Nicola Ferro, Josiane Mothe, Fiana Raiber

